== FROM WORKSTATION MACHINE ==

STEP #1 - Get dashboard
# kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/dashboard/v2.7.0/aio/deploy/recommended.yaml

# kubectl -n kubernetes-dashboard expose deployment kubernetes-dashboard --name k8s-dash --type=NodePort

# kubectl -n kubernetes-dashboard describe svc k8s-dash
<note down the NodePort value>

STEP #2 - run 
kubectl proxy

STEP #3 - Open Browser and access http://127.0.0.1:8001 OR https://<any-node-ip>:NodePort-value

STEP #4 - You need a service account with cluster-admin rights. Create a file dash-srv-account.yaml

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: admin-user
  namespace: kubernetes-dashboard
---
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRoleBinding
metadata:
  name: admin-user
roleRef:
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: cluster-admin
subjects:
- kind: ServiceAccount
  name: admin-user
  namespace: kubernetes-dashboard

## file end here
and apply it - kubectl create -f dash-srv-account.yaml

STEP #5 - Create token for the user created
kubectl -n kubernetes-dashboard create token admin-user

STEP #6 - Now paste the "token" in the authentication method in browser

